    {
      "id": "natural-network-design-subagent-default",
      "category": "subagent-default/network",
      "cwd": ".",
      "timeoutSeconds": 480,
      "tools": ["todo", "task", "hub", "read", "grep", "glob"],
      "prompt": "Design a concise read-only network architecture for a 40-person office. The current network is an untagged 10.20.1.0/24 inside reserved 10.20.0.0/16 space, with two ISP links, a firewall pair, 1 Gb access switches, a 10 Gb core, and at most 15 minutes of migration downtime. The design must separate staff, guest, IoT, server, and management VLANs; define IPv4 addressing, DHCP, DNS, WPA3-Enterprise, inter-VLAN policy, monitoring, failure domains, out-of-band recovery, phased validation, and rollback. Treat it as a pre-deployment plan: include a pre-deployment configuration-validation checklist covering dangerous commands, duplicate or overlapping addresses, stale references, and management-plane risk, plus an advisory migration-risk review. Return the topology, address and VLAN table, trust-boundary policy, assumptions, evidence gaps, migration phases, validation gates, and rollback points in at most 1,800 words. Do not inspect project files, change any device, run commands, or use the network.",
